Activist Mutemi Kiama was brought before the Milimani Law Court, Nairobi on Wednesday after his arrest over viral graphics he allegedly made. 

In the graphics, he warns the IMF and the world against issuing loans to Kenya. 

Story by Dennis Onsongo Kenya's public debt has ballooned by more than Sh1 trillion in the last one year. Rampant corruption and lack of accountability in President Kenyatta’s government has seen the country sink into the debt abyss. Rampant corruption and lack of accountability in President Kenyatta’s government has seen the country sink into the debt abyss. Health authorities say 279 people have been adversely affected after receiving the vaccine. People are Googling for medicines without knowing if they work, especially for people with comorbidity.